 To specify how many GPUs a serve deployment needs, you can use the `ray_actor_options` parameter in the `@serve.deployment` decorator and set the `num_gpus` field to the desired number of GPUs. For example:
```
@serve.deployment(ray_actor_options={"num_gpus": 1})
def func(*args):
    return do_something_with_my_gpu()
```
This will create a deployment with one replica that uses one GPU. You can also set the `num_gpus` field to a fractional value to pack multiple replicas together on a machine with fewer GPUs than replicas. For example:
```
@serve.deployment(ray_actor_options={"num_gpus": 0.5})
def func_2(*args):
    return do_something_with_my_gpu()
```
This will create a deployment with two replicas that each use 0.5 GPUs.

You can also use the `num_gpus` field in the `rayActorOptions` parameter when creating a deployment using the `Serve.deployment()` method. For example:
```
rayActorOptions = {"num_gpus": 1}
Serve.deployment()
    .setName("counter")
    .setDeploymentDef(Counter.class.getName())
    .setRayActorOptions(rayActorOptions)
    .create()
    .deploy(true);
```
This will create a deployment with one replica that uses one GPU.
